posts.question: The "How to Train Your Ninja" comic is getting a lot of backlash probably largely because Asian people in Western countries are minorities and therefore Westerners are seeing that comic in a very different context than the one you created it in. It's a cute comic and especially understanding that you're Asian I don't believe there is anything wrong with it in and of itself but you seemed confused about the backlash you got on it and I wanted to offer up some perspective.
posts.answer: Thank you for your feedback! I talked to my friends(they are all Asians)about this. One of my friends thought Asians have a different point of view on the relationship between couple. But that just her opinion, we all take that comic as a joke. LOL

posts.summary:
Small story behind this!
 This comic idea came to me when I thought that Genji would find troublesome walking in public again,...
posts.caption:
blacksmiley-c:

Small story behind this!

This comic idea came to me when I thought that Genji would find troublesome walking in public again, not feeling like his old self anymore. They all struggled and tried to convince him to go out, but found himself one day taken downtown by Mercy, who needed an extra hand to help her with some grocery shopping. She used as excuse the fact that many of those at the base were either resting after missions, away in missions or just home, enjoying some free days. (everyone needs to relax once in a while XD) Genji always appreciated her care for him, how much time she always spent making sure he did his daily exercises during the recovery period (McCree also helped, and Gabe whenever he had time to spare), and of course the very fact that she made him “exist” again, so he couldn’t refuse her small wish, even if this meant going outside the base. (he was still fresh after recovery.. no missions or such things yet)

—-

I like large hoodies! One of my weak points XD

Made this one quick, before leaving work.

posts.summary: would you mind sharing what the cool present was?
posts.question: would you mind sharing what the cool present was?
posts.answer:
chgreenblatt:

It was a custom version of the game One Night Ultimate Werewolf, with a Harvey Beaks theme. This is a game the crew would play quite often so it has a lot of special meaning. And they fact that they spent seven months secretly putting this together for me makes it even cooler! It’s a perfect homage to both the game and the show.

It’s amazing.

Isn’t this awesome!? I did the lineart for the Fee werewolf card. I can’t believe how perfect everything came out! I feel emotional when I look at it…


WE LOVE YOU CARL!!!!! I’m so happy I got to be part of this show and family :’D

posts.caption:
chgreenblatt:

Here are some fun models from Jeremy: Defender of The Forest. This episode was based off a drawing by Madeleine Flores from when she worked on the show. I promised her we’d make a story around it for season 2. Shane Houghton wrote the outline. Aaron Austin and Hannah Ayoubi wrote and drew the board and Serapio Calm did the final designs.

posts.summary: Happy World Diabetes day!!! I’ve been type 1 diabetic for 17 years. Type 1 diabetes (also called juvenile diabetes) only effects...
posts.caption:
Happy World Diabetes day!!!

I’ve been type 1 diabetic for 17 years. Type 1 diabetes (also called juvenile diabetes) only effects 5% of all diabetics. Most people only know about the 95%, type 2 diabetes (also called adult onset diabetes). Doctors to this day still don’t know what causes type 1.

Basically, it’s just a huge pain in the butt. But I’m so thankful for all the advances in medicine that have been made toward making this incredibly annoying disease a little more manageable.
